{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Q6bxjMKBV8YuTXXV7esjbu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# order-quarkus\n     2→\n     3→This project uses Quarkus, the Supersonic Subatomic Java Framework.\n     4→\n     5→If you want to learn more about Quarkus, please visit its website: <https://quarkus.io/>.\n     6→\n     7→## Running the application in dev mode\n     8→\n     9→You can run your application in dev mode that enables live coding using:\n    10→\n    11→```shell script\n    12→./mvnw quarkus:dev\n    13→```\n    14→\n    15→> **_NOTE:_**  Quarkus now ships with a Dev UI, which is available in dev mode only at <http://localhost:8080/q/dev/>.\n    16→\n    17→## Packaging and running the application\n    18→\n    19→The application can be packaged using:\n    20→\n    21→```shell script\n    22→./mvnw package\n    23→```\n    24→\n    25→It produces the `quarkus-run.jar` file in the `target/quarkus-app/` directory.\n    26→Be aware that it’s not an _über-jar_ as the dependencies are copied into the `target/quarkus-app/lib/` directory.\n    27→\n    28→The application is now runnable using `java -jar target/quarkus-app/quarkus-run.jar`.\n    29→\n    30→If you want to build an _über-jar_, execute the following command:\n    31→\n    32→```shell script\n    33→./mvnw package -Dquarkus.package.jar.type=uber-jar\n    34→```\n    35→\n    36→The application, packaged as an _über-jar_, is now runnable using `java -jar target/*-runner.jar`.\n    37→\n    38→## Creating a native executable\n    39→\n    40→You can create a native executable using:\n    41→\n    42→```shell script\n    43→./mvnw package -Dnative\n    44→```\n    45→\n    46→Or, if you don't have GraalVM installed, you can run the native executable build in a container using:\n    47→\n    48→```shell script\n    49→./mvnw package -Dnative -Dquarkus.native.container-build=true\n    50→```\n    51→\n    52→You can then execute your native executable with: `./target/order-quarkus-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT-runner`\n    53→\n    54→If you want to learn more about building native executables, please consult <https://quarkus.io/guides/maven-tooling>.\n    55→\n    56→## Provided Code\n    57→\n    58→### REST\n    59→\n    60→Easily start your REST Web Services\n    61→\n    62→[Related guide section...](https://quarkus.io/guides/getting-started-reactive#reactive-jax-rs-resources)\n    63→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015SpBXrAf2izpCWK8tU3TqS","session_id":"380c2ee0-cd4b-46ce-87c8-68ac4fb04c36","uuid":"9b488c11-75f1-4971-ba1f-e85c25fbf3b9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015SpBXrAf2izpCWK8tU3TqS","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summary of Findings:\n\n1. Project Structure:\n   - This is a Quarkus-based Java web application for order management\n   - Uses Maven as the build system (pom.xml)\n   - Employs Hibernate ORM for persistence\n   - Uses H2 in-memory database\n   - Implements a web interface with Qute templating\n   - Provides REST endpoints for order and line item management\n\n2. Key Components:\n   - Entities: CustomerOrder, LineItem, Part, Vendor, VendorPart\n   - Repositories for database operations\n   - Web controllers for handling HTTP requests\n   - HTML templates for rendering views\n\n3. Configuration:\n   - Uses H2 in-memory database\n   - Runs on port 8082\n   - Hibernate ORM configured with update schema generation\n   - SQL logging enabled\n\n4. Dockerization:\n   - Multiple Dockerfiles for different deployment scenarios (JVM, native)\n   - Main Dockerfile sets up a development environment with Maven and necessary tools\n\n5. Development and Deployment:\n   - Can be run in dev mode with `./mvnw quarkus:dev`\n   - Packaged as a standard JAR or über-JAR\n   - Supports native executable compilation\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of this project?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"380c2ee0-cd4b-46ce-87c8-68ac4fb04c36","uuid":"fd20e604-cb9e-435d-aa92-b42bb71b0a47"}
