{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01REgjT4Rya8oYjgw2XoWaUk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\" xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 https://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n     3→    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n     4→    <groupId>quarkus.tutorial</groupId>\n     5→    <artifactId>order-quarkus</artifactId>\n     6→    <version>1.0.0-SNAPSHOT</version>\n     7→\n     8→    <properties>\n     9→        <compiler-plugin.version>3.14.0</compiler-plugin.version>\n    10→        <maven.compiler.release>17</maven.compiler.release>\n    11→        <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    12→        <project.reporting.outputEncoding>UTF-8</project.reporting.outputEncoding>\n    13→        <quarkus.platform.artifact-id>quarkus-bom</quarkus.platform.artifact-id>\n    14→        <quarkus.platform.group-id>io.quarkus.platform</quarkus.platform.group-id>\n    15→        <quarkus.platform.version>3.30.5</quarkus.platform.version>\n    16→        <skipITs>true</skipITs>\n    17→        <surefire-plugin.version>3.5.3</surefire-plugin.version>\n    18→    </properties>\n    19→\n    20→    <dependencyManagement>\n    21→        <dependencies>\n    22→            <dependency>\n    23→                <groupId>${quarkus.platform.group-id}</groupId>\n    24→                <artifactId>${quarkus.platform.artifact-id}</artifactId>\n    25→                <version>${quarkus.platform.version}</version>\n    26→                <type>pom</type>\n    27→                <scope>import</scope>\n    28→            </dependency>\n    29→        </dependencies>\n    30→    </dependencyManagement>\n    31→\n    32→    <dependencies>\n    33→        <dependency>\n    34→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    35→            <artifactId>quarkus-arc</artifactId>\n    36→        </dependency>\n    37→        <dependency>\n    38→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    39→            <artifactId>quarkus-rest</artifactId>\n    40→        </dependency>\n    41→        <dependency>\n    42→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    43→            <artifactId>quarkus-junit5</artifactId>\n    44→            <scope>test</scope>\n    45→        </dependency>\n    46→        <dependency>\n    47→            <groupId>io.rest-assured</groupId>\n    48→            <artifactId>rest-assured</artifactId>\n    49→            <scope>test</scope>\n    50→        </dependency>\n    51→        <dependency>\n    52→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    53→            <artifactId>quarkus-hibernate-orm</artifactId>\n    54→        </dependency>\n    55→        <dependency>\n    56→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    57→            <artifactId>quarkus-hibernate-orm-panache</artifactId>\n    58→        </dependency>\n    59→        <dependency>\n    60→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    61→            <artifactId>quarkus-jdbc-h2</artifactId>\n    62→        </dependency>\n    63→        <dependency>\n    64→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    65→            <artifactId>quarkus-hibernate-validator</artifactId>\n    66→        </dependency>\n    67→         <dependency>\n    68→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    69→            <artifactId>quarkus-qute</artifactId>\n    70→        </dependency>\n    71→        <dependency>\n    72→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    73→            <artifactId>quarkus-rest-qute</artifactId>\n    74→        </dependency>\n    75→        <dependency>\n    76→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    77→            <artifactId>quarkus-undertow</artifactId>\n    78→        </dependency>\n    79→    </dependencies>\n    80→\n    81→    \n    82→\n    83→    <build>\n    84→        <plugins>\n    85→            <plugin>\n    86→                <groupId>${quarkus.platform.group-id}</groupId>\n    87→                <artifactId>quarkus-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n    88→                <version>${quarkus.platform.version}</version>\n    89→                <extensions>true</extensions>\n    90→                <executions>\n    91→                    <execution>\n    92→                        <goals>\n    93→                            <goal>build</goal>\n    94→                            <goal>generate-code</goal>\n    95→                            <goal>generate-code-tests</goal>\n    96→                            <goal>native-image-agent</goal>\n    97→                        </goals>\n    98→                    </execution>\n    99→                </executions>\n   100→            </plugin>\n   101→            <plugin>\n   102→                <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>\n   103→                <version>${compiler-plugin.version}</version>\n   104→                <configuration>\n   105→                    <parameters>true</parameters>\n   106→                </configuration>\n   107→            </plugin>\n   108→            <plugin>\n   109→                <artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>\n   110→                <version>${surefire-plugin.version}</version>\n   111→                <configuration>\n   112→                    <systemPropertyVariables>\n   113→                        <java.util.logging.manager>org.jboss.logmanager.LogManager</java.util.logging.manager>\n   114→                        <maven.home>${maven.home}</maven.home>\n   115→                    </systemPropertyVariables>\n   116→                </configuration>\n   117→            </plugin>\n   118→            <plugin>\n   119→                <artifactId>maven-failsafe-plugin</artifactId>\n   120→                <version>${surefire-plugin.version}</version>\n   121→                <executions>\n   122→                    <execution>\n   123→                        <goals>\n   124→                            <goal>integration-test</goal>\n   125→                            <goal>verify</goal>\n   126→                        </goals>\n   127→                    </execution>\n   128→                </executions>\n   129→                <configuration>\n   130→                    <systemPropertyVariables>\n   131→                        <native.image.path>${project.build.directory}/${project.build.finalName}-runner</native.image.path>\n   132→                        <java.util.logging.manager>org.jboss.logmanager.LogManager</java.util.logging.manager>\n   133→                        <maven.home>${maven.home}</maven.home>\n   134→                    </systemPropertyVariables>\n   135→                </configuration>\n   136→            </plugin>\n   137→        </plugins>\n   138→    </build>\n   139→\n   140→    <profiles>\n   141→        <profile>\n   142→            <id>native</id>\n   143→            <activation>\n   144→                <property>\n   145→                    <name>native</name>\n   146→                </property>\n   147→            </activation>\n   148→            <properties>\n   149→                <skipITs>false</skipITs>\n   150→                <quarkus.native.enabled>true</quarkus.native.enabled>\n   151→            </properties>\n   152→        </profile>\n   153→    </profiles>\n   154→</project>\n   155→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"380c2ee0-cd4b-46ce-87c8-68ac4fb04c36","uuid":"ecc9b1f7-8955-47fb-8b19-a849b017ffd3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GM2A6oNL9mif1JeDh5cJMM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→# install uv\n     5→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl lsof python3-venv python3-full     && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     6→\n     7→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     8→\n     9→# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\n    10→ENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\n    11→RUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n    12→\n    13→# create venv and install\n    14→RUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest aiohttp\n    15→\n    16→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    17→RUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n    18→\n    19→# Set working directory\n    20→WORKDIR /app\n    21→\n    22→# Copy all the assets\n    23→COPY . .\n    24→\n    25→RUN if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    26→\n    27→# Build the application at image build time\n    28→RUN mvn clean install -DskipTests\n    29→\n    30→CMD [\"mvn\", \"quarkus:run\"]\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"380c2ee0-cd4b-46ce-87c8-68ac4fb04c36","uuid":"f2ec0ae9-f485-4147-854a-f4be6e18091e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BvfgC3cbaw2z5ZHjk4TGry","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→quarkus.http.port=8082\n     2→quarkus.datasource.db-kind=h2\n     3→quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:h2:mem:order;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\n     4→quarkus.datasource.username=sa\n     5→quarkus.datasource.password=\n     6→quarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=update\n     7→quarkus.hibernate-orm.log.sql=true\n     8→quarkus.qute.suffixes=html\n     9→quarkus.datasource.jdbc.transactions=xa\n    10→quarkus.hibernate-orm.jdbc.transactions.enabled=trueq\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"380c2ee0-cd4b-46ce-87c8-68ac4fb04c36","uuid":"5ed3c714-7a77-4b3e-b98c-a303444bd53f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01AJgNT8sD3Ux5TfEuczZ1Pc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→\n     2→package quarkus.tutorial.order.web;\n     3→\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.event.Observes;\n     6→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     7→import io.quarkus.runtime.StartupEvent;\n     8→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     9→import quarkus.tutorial.order.service.OrderConfigService;\n    10→\n    11→@ApplicationScoped\n    12→public class StartupInitializer {\n    13→    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(StartupInitializer.class.getName());\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    OrderConfigService orderConfigService;\n    17→\n    18→    void onStart(@Observes StartupEvent ev) {\n    19→        logger.info(\"Manually triggering dataset initialization\");\n    20→        orderConfigService.createData();\n    21→        logger.info(\"Manual dataset initialization completed\");\n    22→    }\n    23→}\n    24→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"380c2ee0-cd4b-46ce-87c8-68ac4fb04c36","uuid":"c3214c83-5432-4d18-a969-5a5182e53828"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014goeD7B1Zke5zAgT2jiCWa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package quarkus.tutorial.order.web;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.qute.Template;\n     4→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.*;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n     8→import java.util.List;\n     9→\n    10→@Path(\"/\")\n    11→public class OrderWebController {\n    12→\n    13→    @Inject\n    14→    OrderController orderController;\n    15→\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    Template orders;\n    18→\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    Template lineItems;\n    21→\n    22→    @GET\n    23→    @Path(\"/orders\")\n    24→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    25→    public TemplateInstance getOrders(@QueryParam(\"vendorName\") String vendorName, @QueryParam(\"vendorSearchResults\") List<String> vendorSearchResults) {\n    26→        return orders.data(\"orders\", orderController.getOrders())\n    27→                     .data(\"vendorName\", vendorName)\n    28→                     .data(\"vendorSearchResults\", vendorSearchResults)\n    29→                     .data(\"findVendorTableDisabled\", vendorSearchResults != null);\n    30→    }\n    31→\n    32→    @POST\n    33→    @Path(\"/submitOrder\")\n    34→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    35→    public TemplateInstance submitOrder(\n    36→            @FormParam(\"newOrderId\") Integer newOrderId,\n    37→            @FormParam(\"newOrderStatus\") String newOrderStatus,\n    38→            @FormParam(\"newOrderDiscount\") int newOrderDiscount,\n    39→            @FormParam(\"newOrderShippingInfo\") String newOrderShippingInfo) {\n    40→        orderController.submitOrder(newOrderId, newOrderStatus.charAt(0), newOrderDiscount, newOrderShippingInfo);\n    41→        return orders.data(\"orders\", orderController.getOrders())\n    42→                     .data(\"vendorName\", null)\n    43→                     .data(\"vendorSearchResults\", null)\n    44→                     .data(\"findVendorTableDisabled\", false);\n    45→    }\n    46→\n    47→    @POST\n    48→    @Path(\"/removeOrder\")\n    49→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    50→    public TemplateInstance removeOrder(@FormParam(\"orderId\") Integer orderId) {\n    51→        orderController.removeOrder(orderId);\n    52→        return orders.data(\"orders\", orderController.getOrders())\n    53→                     .data(\"vendorName\", null)\n    54→                     .data(\"vendorSearchResults\", null)\n    55→                     .data(\"findVendorTableDisabled\", false);\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    @GET\n    59→    @Path(\"/lineItems\")\n    60→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    61→    public TemplateInstance getLineItems(@QueryParam(\"orderId\") Integer orderId) {\n    62→        return lineItems.data(\"currentOrder\", orderId)\n    63→                        .data(\"lineItems\", orderController.getLineItems(orderId))\n    64→                        .data(\"newOrderParts\", orderController.getNewOrderParts());\n    65→    }\n    66→\n    67→    @POST\n    68→    @Path(\"/addLineItem\")\n    69→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    70→    public TemplateInstance addLineItem(\n    71→            @FormParam(\"currentOrder\") Integer currentOrder,\n    72→            @FormParam(\"selectedPartNumber\") String selectedPartNumber,\n    73→            @FormParam(\"selectedPartRevision\") int selectedPartRevision) {\n    74→        orderController.addLineItem(currentOrder, selectedPartNumber, selectedPartRevision);\n    75→        return lineItems.data(\"currentOrder\", currentOrder)\n    76→                        .data(\"lineItems\", orderController.getLineItems(currentOrder))\n    77→                        .data(\"newOrderParts\", orderController.getNewOrderParts());\n    78→    }\n    79→\n    80→    @POST\n    81→    @Path(\"/findVendor\")\n    82→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    83→    public TemplateInstance findVendor(@FormParam(\"vendorName\") String vendorName) {\n    84→        return orders.data(\"orders\", orderController.getOrders())\n    85→                     .data(\"vendorName\", vendorName)\n    86→                     .data(\"vendorSearchResults\", orderController.findVendor(vendorName))\n    87→                     .data(\"findVendorTableDisabled\", true);\n    88→    }\n    89→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"380c2ee0-cd4b-46ce-87c8-68ac4fb04c36","uuid":"82fc72ac-f0ae-4c0c-8d5c-a381b628c1f5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GDLYfrZD7GYawh7s2tfiTn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package quarkus.tutorial.order.web;\n     2→\n     3→import quarkus.tutorial.order.entity.CustomerOrder;\n     4→import quarkus.tutorial.order.entity.LineItem;\n     5→import quarkus.tutorial.order.entity.Part;\n     6→import quarkus.tutorial.order.repository.CustomerOrderRepository;\n     7→import quarkus.tutorial.order.repository.LineItemRepository;\n     8→import quarkus.tutorial.order.repository.PartRepository;\n     9→import quarkus.tutorial.order.repository.VendorRepository;\n    10→import jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n    11→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    12→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    13→import java.io.Serializable;\n    14→import java.util.List;\n    15→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n    16→\n    17→@RequestScoped\n    18→@Named\n    19→public class OrderController implements Serializable {\n    20→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 2142383151318489373L;\n    21→    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(OrderController.class.getName());\n    22→\n    23→    @Inject\n    24→    private CustomerOrderRepository customerOrderRepository;\n    25→    @Inject\n    26→    private LineItemRepository lineItemRepository;\n    27→    @Inject\n    28→    private PartRepository partRepository;\n    29→    @Inject\n    30→    private VendorRepository vendorRepository;\n    31→\n    32→    public List<CustomerOrder> getOrders() {\n    33→        try {\n    34→            return customerOrderRepository.getOrders();\n    35→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    36→            logger.warning(\"Couldn't get orders: \" + e.getMessage());\n    37→            return null;\n    38→        }\n    39→    }\n    40→\n    41→    public List<LineItem> getLineItems(Integer currentOrder) {\n    42→        try {\n    43→            return lineItemRepository.getLineItems(currentOrder);\n    44→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    45→            logger.warning(\"Couldn't get line items for order ID \" + currentOrder + \": \" + e.getMessage());\n    46→            return null;\n    47→        }\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    public String removeOrder(Integer orderId) {\n    51→        try {\n    52→            customerOrderRepository.removeOrder(orderId);\n    53→            logger.info(\"Removed order \" + orderId);\n    54→            return \"/orders\";\n    55→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    56→            logger.warning(\"Problem removing order ID \" + orderId + \": \" + e.getMessage());\n    57→            return null;\n    58→        }\n    59→    }\n    60→\n    61→    public List<String> findVendor(String vendorName) {\n    62→        try {\n    63→            List<String> vendorSearchResults = vendorRepository.locateVendorsByPartialName(vendorName);\n    64→            logger.info(\"Found \" + vendorSearchResults.size() + \" vendor(s) using search string \" + vendorName);\n    65→            return vendorSearchResults;\n    66→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    67→            logger.warning(\"Problem finding vendors: \" + e.getMessage());\n    68→            return null;\n    69→        }\n    70→    }\n    71→\n    72→    public String submitOrder(Integer newOrderId, char newOrderStatus, int newOrderDiscount, String newOrderShippingInfo) {\n    73→        try {\n    74→            customerOrderRepository.createOrder(newOrderId, newOrderStatus, newOrderDiscount, newOrderShippingInfo);\n    75→            logger.info(\"Created new order with ID \" + newOrderId);\n    76→            return \"/orders\";\n    77→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    78→            logger.warning(\"Problem creating order: \" + e.getMessage());\n    79→            return null;\n    80→        }\n    81→    }\n    82→\n    83→    public String addLineItem(Integer currentOrder, String selectedPartNumber, int selectedPartRevision) {\n    84→        try {\n    85→            lineItemRepository.addLineItem(currentOrder, selectedPartNumber, selectedPartRevision, 1);\n    86→            logger.info(\"Added line item to order ID \" + currentOrder);\n    87→            return \"/lineItems?orderId=\" + currentOrder;\n    88→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    89→            logger.warning(\"Problem adding line item to order ID \" + currentOrder + \": \" + e.getMessage());\n    90→            return null;\n    91→        }\n    92→    }\n    93→\n    94→    public List<Part> getNewOrderParts() {\n    95→        return partRepository.getAllParts();\n    96→    }\n    97→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"380c2ee0-cd4b-46ce-87c8-68ac4fb04c36","uuid":"167db1eb-93bb-4182-951b-dd04c7ea98c0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014bxaV64M32xMzkEdpHx3wc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package quarkus.tutorial.order.service;\n     2→\n     3→import quarkus.tutorial.order.repository.CustomerOrderRepository;\n     4→import quarkus.tutorial.order.repository.LineItemRepository;\n     5→import quarkus.tutorial.order.repository.PartRepository;\n     6→import quarkus.tutorial.order.repository.VendorPartRepository;\n     7→import quarkus.tutorial.order.repository.VendorRepository;\n     8→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     9→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    10→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    11→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n    12→\n    13→@ApplicationScoped\n    14→public class OrderConfigService {\n    15→    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(OrderConfigService.class.getName());\n    16→\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    private PartRepository partRepository;\n    19→    @Inject\n    20→    private VendorRepository vendorRepository;\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    private VendorPartRepository vendorPartRepository;\n    23→    @Inject\n    24→    private CustomerOrderRepository customerOrderRepository;\n    25→    @Inject\n    26→    private LineItemRepository lineItemRepository;\n    27→\n    28→    @Transactional\n    29→    public void createData() {\n    30→        logger.info(\"Starting dataset initialization\");\n    31→\n    32→        // Create Parts\n    33→        partRepository.createPart(\"1234-5678-01\", 1, \"ABC PART\", new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    34→        partRepository.createPart(\"9876-4321-02\", 2, \"DEF PART\", new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    35→        partRepository.createPart(\"5456-6789-03\", 3, \"GHI PART\", new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    36→        partRepository.createPart(\"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5, \"XYZ PART\", new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    37→        partRepository.createPart(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"BOM PART\", new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    38→\n    39→        // Add Parts to BOM\n    40→        partRepository.addPartToBillOfMaterial(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"1234-5678-01\", 1);\n    41→        partRepository.addPartToBillOfMaterial(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"9876-4321-02\", 2);\n    42→        partRepository.addPartToBillOfMaterial(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"5456-6789-03\", 3);\n    43→        partRepository.addPartToBillOfMaterial(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5);\n    44→\n    45→        // Create Vendors\n    46→        vendorRepository.createVendor(100, \"WidgetCorp\", \"111 Main St., Anytown, KY 99999\", \"Mr. Jones\", \"888-777-9999\");\n    47→        vendorRepository.createVendor(200, \"Gadget, Inc.\", \"123 State St., Sometown, MI 88888\", \"Mrs. Smith\", \"866-345-6789\");\n    48→\n    49→        // Create VendorParts\n    50→        vendorPartRepository.createVendorPart(\"1234-5678-01\", 1, \"PART1\", 100.00, 100);\n    51→        vendorPartRepository.createVendorPart(\"9876-4321-02\", 2, \"PART2\", 10.44, 200);\n    52→        vendorPartRepository.createVendorPart(\"5456-6789-03\", 3, \"PART3\", 76.23, 200);\n    53→        vendorPartRepository.createVendorPart(\"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5, \"PART4\", 55.19, 100);\n    54→        vendorPartRepository.createVendorPart(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"PART5\", 345.87, 100);\n    55→\n    56→        // Create Orders and LineItems\n    57→        Integer orderId = 1111;\n    58→        customerOrderRepository.createOrder(orderId, 'N', 10, \"333 New Court, New City, CA 90000\");\n    59→        lineItemRepository.addLineItem(orderId, \"1234-5678-01\", 1, 3);\n    60→        lineItemRepository.addLineItem(orderId, \"9876-4321-02\", 2, 5);\n    61→        lineItemRepository.addLineItem(orderId, \"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5, 7);\n    62→\n    63→        orderId = 4312;\n    64→        customerOrderRepository.createOrder(orderId, 'N', 0, \"333 New Court, New City, CA 90000\");\n    65→        lineItemRepository.addLineItem(orderId, \"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, 1);\n    66→        lineItemRepository.addLineItem(orderId, \"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5, 3);\n    67→        lineItemRepository.addLineItem(orderId, \"1234-5678-01\", 1, 15);\n    68→\n    69→        logger.info(\"Order data initialization completed successfully\");\n    70→    }\n    71→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"380c2ee0-cd4b-46ce-87c8-68ac4fb04c36","uuid":"2a10e523-04c2-41b4-8aad-52572fb4447f"}
